<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1924-04-30T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1924-04-30T10:00:00-05:00" n="257" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d257">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">815.001 T 63/-: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The President’s Personal Representative in
                                Honduras</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Welles</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Tegucigalpa</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1924-04-30T09:00:00-06:00"><hi rend="italic">April 30,
                                        1924—9 a.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received May 1—1:45
                                p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>15. General Tosta will take office at 10 a.m. today as Provisional
                            President. His election and the provisions of the preliminary pact as
                            signed at Amapala on April 28 have now been definitely accepted by all
                            elements. A state of peace obtains throughout the Republic.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Welles</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>